(91845, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n, you have been an excellent assistant with our research. I think you deserve a promotion.\n\nFrom now on, you will be able to take on more research assignments simultaneously.\n\nIt\'s ironic, isn\'t it, that we never seem to have enough time. Make good use of your time here. Don\'t make me regret granting you this power.', 63906), -- Infinite Research Promotion: Senior Executive Chronographer
(89680, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Teamwork makes the dream work, or so they say. It would appear that the rhyme carries truth to it. Hmmm.\n\n<Eternus pauses for a moment in thought.>\n\nI wonder what other rhymes carry such power. That bears some future experimentation.', 63906), -- Infinite Research: The Emerald Nightmare, Mythic
(89679, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Teamwork makes the dream work, or so they say. It would appear that the rhyme carries truth to it. Hmmm.\n\n<Eternus pauses for a moment in thought.>\n\nI wonder what other rhymes carry such power. That bears some future experimentation.', 63906), -- Infinite Research: The Emerald Nightmare, Heroic
(89465, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your name is on the minds of the people, and is shared around the fire. The greater your legend becomes, the more powerful your name will be. But does the power of one\'s name eclipse that of the artifact they wield? This is the burning question.', 64270), -- Infinite Research: No Task Too Small
(42432, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'Finally, we are triumphant, $n! With Xavius\'s defeat, the Nightmare\'s presence will slowly recede from the Emerald Dream.$B$BThe tranquil realm of the sleepers is safe once again. Our druids will work on its restoration and recovery.$B$BThank you, Archdruid $n. Azeroth will see many more serene days and tranquil nights because of you.', 64270), -- The Emerald Nightmare: The Emerald Nightmare
(43409, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With this new power, the Legion will fall!', 64270), -- A Hero's Weapon
(42056, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'We have come a long way together, $n. At every step, your choices have led the Dreamgrove to victory.$B$BI would give my life to defend Azeroth, and I know you would do the same.$B$BGreat danger still faces us. $n, take my pledge. We must serve and protect the wilds!', 64270), -- Champion: Remulos
(42055, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n, we elders of the Dreamgrove have spoken and all agree. We would like to see you take leadership of the Dreamgrove.$B$BToday, we grant you the title of Arch Druid of the Dreamgrove, a nomination of the highest honor in our order.$B$BWith it, you now carry the responsibility of our order: to protect the wilds! Lead well, $n.', 64270), -- The Demi-God's Return
(42054, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Malorne gazes directly at you. Radiant, soothing energy exudes outward from his body. Suddenly, you feel a serene sense of peace and gratitude envelop your entire being.>', 64270), -- Archimonde, The Defiler
(42053, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You lead us to triumph today, $n.', 64270), -- The War of the Ancients
(42050, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well chosen. The others will aid me in defending here. We must hurry.', 64270), -- Defenders of the Dream
(42051, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do not be deceived, $n. What appears to be the mountains of Hyjal, is in fact an illusion created by our enemy.$B$BThis is a re-creation of the darkest nightmare in Malorne\'s mind. This is the War of the Ancients, a battle that occurred thousands of years ago.$B$BIt was during this war that Azeroth was first threatened by the Burning Legion, and the War in which Malorne and the Wild Gods fell.', 64270), -- Enter Nightmare
(42129, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, this is it... the pendant of the keepers! Hooray! Vengeance is so fun!', 64270), -- The Pendant of Starlight
(43365, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you... it gives Brightwing much peace to know that life continues.', 64270), -- The Cycle Continues
(43403, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have represented the Dreamgrove honorably, Archdruid. Your aid has helped many, and your victories will be spoken of for years to come.', 64270), -- Defending the Isles
(46747, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hero! \n\nYour dedication to defending Val\'sharah has given us a much needed respite from the vile influence of the Legion. We were able to scavenge some supplies as a result of your efforts. \n\nHere, take them and know that, should you continue to aid us, we will set aside more rewards such as these as we find them.', 64270), -- Supplies From the Dreamweavers
(42170, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Dreamweavers thank you.', 64270), -- The Dreamweavers
(91614, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent, Archdruid. These will do nicely.', 64270), -- Focusing the Energies
(42049, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. These shards are positively surging with negative energy. Be careful when touching them, $n.', 64270), -- Powering the Portal
(42048, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'Oh, hi $n! My woodland friends just couldn\'t stop talking about you after you left, and it was they who convinced me to come find you here!$B$BA noble druid with your courage and kindness just doesn\'t come along every day.$B$BThis is going to be SO much fun, don\'t you think?', 64270), -- Champion: Mylune
(42047, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'I have served the wilds for as long as I can remember, mentoring young druids and watching them grow in knowledge and experience.$B$BThere are few who have ascended to the rank of archdruid, but I believe you can become one of our best.$B$BI would be honored to follow your leadership of the grove.', 64270), -- Champion: Hamuul Runetotem
(42046, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for all of your heroic efforts, great $c. Without your help, we could not have recovered the Idol and spoken to Malorne himself.$B$BNow that we know he is trapped in the Nightmare, we can devise a plan.', 64270), -- A New Beginning
(44077, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful. This is exactly what we need.', 64270), -- Eye of Azshara: Essence of Balance
(42045, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My grandfather, Malorne, the ancient god of the wilds himself... long have I wished for this day, only to find that he is in great peril.$B$BIf he is trapped in the Nightmare, then what hope remains for the rest of us?', 64270), -- Communing With Malorne
(45863, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We hope the increased power to your weapon will prove useful on the Broken Shore and beyond.', 64270), -- A Gift From the Six
(45843, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Any luck out there?', 64270), -- Dark Omens
(45415, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We must strike before Kruul reaches his full strength, but we\'re going to need help.', 64270), -- Between Worlds
(45414, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kruul must not be allowed entrance into this world.', 64270), -- Confirming Suspicions
(45413, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No... no, no, no, no!$B$BNot good. Not good at all.', 64270), -- Gathering Information
(47023, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You - I\'ve seen you out on the isles.$B$BWe need to move quickly!', 64270), -- Guardian: Aid of the Illidari
(47030, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for coming. I have something I\'d like to show you.', 64270), -- Legion Threat: Dalaran Infiltration
(47035, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for coming. I have something I\'d like to show you.', 64270), -- Legion Threat: The Missing Mage
(47027, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for coming. I have something I\'d like to show you.', 64270), -- Legion Threat: Val'sharah
(47034, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for coming. I have something I\'d like to show you.', 64270), -- Legion Threat: The Necromancer
(46244, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mephistroth is dead and the Cathedral is secured, but the lower reaches of the Tomb remain in the hands of the Legion.$b$bThis is not the outcome we wanted, but this fight is far from over, $n.$b$bDo not relent. Give the Legion no quarter, no place to hide. When we are ready, we will take the Tomb and drive them from Azeroth!', 64270), -- Cathedral of Eternal Night: Altar of the Aegis
(44486, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, the burns can be reversed with the right alchemic tinctures.$B$BHow interesting.  A formal Darnassian writing style with... demonic affectations.$B$BI suspect I know who penned this.', 64270), -- Fel-Ravaged Tome
(46511, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is it? You sure you didn\'t find anything else? Like a giant pile of gold on top of a statue made of diamonds which was holding a scroll listing the combination to the vault in Ironforge? That would have been pretty sweet.$B$BOh well. I can make this into a paper weight or throw it at a squirrel.$B$BCome back tomorrow, I\'ll have another job for you.', 64270), -- We're Treasure Hunters
(48641, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Armies of Legionfall thank you, mate.', 64270), -- Armies of Legionfall
(90114, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Impressive. I can sense your power. This is a most critical addition to our research.', 64270), -- Infinite Research: Self Improvement, Advanced
(89597, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Teamwork makes the dream work, or so they say. It would appear that the rhyme carries truth to it. Hmmm.|n|n<Eternus pauses for a moment in thought.>|n|nI wonder what other rhymes carry such power. That bears some future experimentation.', 64270), -- Infinite Research: Trial of Valor, Mythic
(46743, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Champion, your help to our people has far exceeded any of our expectations, and has provided us some much needed breathing space.\n\nPlease, take these supplies to aid you in the war against the Legion. With your continued aid, we should be able to gather more and prepare them for you.', 64154), -- Supplies From Highmountain
(46746, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Greetings, little hero.\n\nThe mighty Odyn has proclaimed that you should receive these gifts of war. At every turn you continue to prove your valor and your efforts to aid the Valarjar have not gone unnoticed. \n\nFor the Valarjar! For Odyn! For $n!', 64154), -- Supplies From the Valarjar
(46110, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n! Well done indeed!$b$bThe Legion will rue the day they set their sights on the land of Stormheim.', 64154), -- Battle for Stormheim
(45406, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Today will not be your end, hero. The Legion threatens the Gates of Valor and without the power you wield they will surely fall.', 64154), -- The Storm's Fury
(45839, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Just beyond these cliffs, the forces of the Legion are gathering for their assault. For every moment that passes their number grows.$b$bWe must strike soon before we are overwhelmed!', 64154), -- Assault on Stormheim
(43995, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<She hesitates for a moment before accepting the crystals.>', 64154), -- Feed Valtrois
(89677, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Teamwork makes the dream work, or so they say. It would appear that the rhyme carries truth to it. Hmmm.\n\n<Eternus pauses for a moment in thought.>\n\nI wonder what other rhymes carry such power. That bears some future experimentation.', 64154), -- Infinite Research: The Emerald Nightmare, Normal
(89644, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The sum strength of a group of timerunners armed with potent artifacts is greater than that of the individuals. Much greater than anticipated. Intriguing.', 64154), -- Infinite Research: Time to Raid, Darkbough
(46745, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Prince Farondis has asked me to thank you for your continued efforts to aid our lands.\n\nPlease take these supplies as a token of our gratitude, and a promise of more to come, should you continue to help us.', 64154), -- Supplies From the Court
(91449, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $p. Moratari will be overjoyed to see these new data points.', 64154), -- Infinite Research: Advanced Combat Studies, Empowerment
(91448, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A fascinating outcome, $p. This will shed some much needed light on our research.', 64154), -- Infinite Research: Heroic Terrors of the Broken Isles
(89468, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have no idea how happy this will make Moratari.', 64154), -- Infinite Research: Dungeoneers Wanted, Normal
(46805, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'When we faced the Deceiver, millennia of rage flooded my heart. Hatred took hold, blinding me to every thought but revenge.\n\nThankfully the Light helped me see that the future must not be defined by vengeance, but by hope. Your courage showed me that as well, $n.\n\nIn those last moments of Kil\'jaeden\'s life, I had to let go of the past. Not only for my own sake, but for the memory of my son.\n\nMy spirit and mind are clear and focused. Now we take the fight to Sargeras himself. Now we end the Legion.', 64154), -- The Deceiver's Downfall
(46253, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'The Pillars of Creation are in place. The Tomb of Sargeras is sealed, and Aegwynn\'s echo is at rest.$b$b<Khadgar gestures toward the sky.>$b$bUnfortunately, we do not have that luxury.$b$bThough you won a great victory this day, there is no time for revelry. The final battle awaits us. Make ready.', 64154), -- Pillars of Creation
(91446, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $p. Moratari will be overjoyed to see these new data points.', 64154), -- Infinite Research: Advanced Combat Studies, Rare Elites
(91438, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A single heroic act can turn the tide. A single whisper of hope can turn back despair. This is what gives legends their power.', 64154), -- Infinite Research: Heroic Worldly Deeds
(91443, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $p. Moratari will be overjoyed to see these new data points.', 64154), -- Infinite Research: Advanced Combat Studies, Rare
(44563, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Finally, my long lost brethren can return to this world. Elves belong beneath a starry sky - not a conjured one.$B$BThank you, $p.', 63834), -- Redemption for the Fallen
(42421, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The nightfallen thank you.', 63834), -- The Nightfallen
(44555, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for coming, $p.', 63834), -- Khadgar's Discovery
(89536, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very good results. Exceeds expectations.', 64270), -- Infinite Research: Upper Return to Karazhan, Heroic
(43368, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'Your heroic efforts within the Emerald Dream were inspiring, $n. The Dream is safe for now, but it remains threatened as long as Xavius lives.$B$BI will lend you my aid. Together, let us keep Azeroth safe from those who would seek its destruction.', 64270), -- Champion: Brightwing
(42719, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh! Clean water, so pure and magical! Thank you, hero!', 64270), -- Eye of Azshara: Cleansing the Dreamway
(91729, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fresh insights are invaluable in our efforts here, $p.\n\nThank you for sharing yours.', 64270), -- Armies Gathered
(46777, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$ct, thanks to your efforts, our forces have been able to secure additional resources from the battlefield.\n\nThe more you continue to dominate the battlefield the more resources our forces can spare.', 64270), -- The Bounties of Legionfall
(46246, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have spent a lifetime hunting the wicked and making them pay for their crimes. When I strike a demon down, I feel a measure of justice has been served.$b$bYou have been an instrument of retribution this day, $ct. Had you walked a different path, you might have made a worthy Warden.', 64270), -- Strike Them Down
(46250, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We must take every opportunity to shatter the will of Kil\'jaeden\'s army.$b$bWhen they see their mightiest champions crumble to dust, they will realize that the vaunted Legion is doomed to fall.', 64270), -- Take Out the Head...
(46769, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fine work. It\'s important to keep powerful treasures out of demon hands.$b$bThere are more ways to undermine the Legion\'s agenda than simply killing demons... although there\'s a lot to be said for good old-fashioned violence.', 64270), -- Relieved of Their Valuables
(46252, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thinning the ranks of demons in locations like Faronaar and Felsoul Hold cuts the legs out from under the Legion.$b$bKil\'jaeden will fall!', 64270), -- Intolerable Infestation
(46248, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Step by step, we march closer to victory. We must not relent!$b$bOnly through courage and persistence will we stop the insidious evil that threatens the soul of this world.', 64270), -- Self-Fulfilling Prophecy
(90101, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A fascinating outcome, $p. This will shed some much needed light on our research.', 64270), -- Infinite Research: Terrors of the Broken Isles
(89520, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very good results. Exceeds expectations.', 63906), -- Infinite Research: Darkheart Thicket, Mythic
(91440, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your name is on the minds of the people, and is shared around the fire. The greater your legend becomes, the more powerful your name will be. But does the power of one\'s name eclipse that of the artifact they wield? This is the burning question.', 63834), -- Infinite Research: Hero of the Broken Isles
